Retrieve information stored a Dissolved Oxygen calibration details file

Source: R/parse_hoboware_details.R
get_do_details.Rd

get_do_details() extracts a specific subset of the information stored in a details file generated by HOBOware during DO calibration.

Usage

get_do_details(path)

Arguments

path

The path to a details file created by HOBOware during calibration.

Value

A nested list containing of a small subset of the information in file.

See also

  • get_cond_details() for a similar function to process a HOBOware details file generated while calibrating conductance/salinity.

  • parse_hoboware_details() for a function to read and format all of the information in a HOBOware details file.

Examples

 file <- system.file(
   "extdata/2023/RB1/2023-06-09/Calibrated/DO_RB1_2023-06-09_Details.txt",
                     package = "BuzzardsBay")
 do_cal  <- get_do_details(file)
 cat(yaml::as.yaml(do_cal))
